  "prompt": "What are 13.1 and 26.2 stickers and what do they mean?",
  "response": "\"13.1\" and \"26.2\" stickers typically refer to the distances of half-marathon and full marathon races, respectively. Here's a breakdown of what they mean:\n\n1. **13.1 Stickers (Half-Marathon):**\n   - **Distance:** 13.1 miles (21.097 kilometers)\n   - **Purpose:** Represent completion or participation in a half-marathon race.\n   - **Usage:** Runners often use these stickers on items like water bottles, running gear, jackets, or bags as a badge of honor or to commemorate their achievement.\n\n2. **26.2 Stickers (Full Marathon):**\n   - **Distance:** 26.2 miles (42.195 kilometers)\n   - **Purpose:** Represent completion or participation in a full marathon race.\n   - **Usage:** Similar to half-marathon stickers, these are used by marathon finishers to display their accomplishment on various personal items.\n\n**Meaning and Significance:**\n\n- **Achievement Recognition:** Obtaining a sticker for running these distances serves as a tangible reminder of the hard work, training, and dedication required to complete such challenging events.\n- **Community and Identity:** Displaying these stickers can help runners identify with a community of fellow runners and showcase their commitment to the sport.\n- **Motivation:** For some, these stickers act as motivation to set and achieve personal fitness goals, whether it's completing their first half-marathon or striving for a marathon.\n\n**Where to Get Them:**\n\n- **Race Events:** Many organized races provide these stickers to participants upon completion, either during the race or at the finish line.\n- **Running Clubs and Stores:** Some running clubs, specialty stores, or online retailers sell stickers catering to various running milestones.\n\nIn summary, \"13.1 and 26.2 stickers\" are emblematic tokens for runners who have participated in half-marathon and full marathon events, symbolizing their endurance and dedication to long-distance running.",
